comentario: This video was inspired by and pays homage to the movie "Death Becomes Her" a fun 80's classic you'll love which stars Goldie Hawn, Meryl Streep, & Bruce Willis. This video is basically a short version remake of the film that uses all the same gags, storyline, setups/pay offs, and digital effects. "Death Becomes Her" is one of my absolute favorite movies from the 80's which I've seen hundreds of times thru years, and Sabrina did such an amazing job recreating it here in this masterpiece! The only difference between the two is Goldie and Meryl don't have a kissing scene.  You guys have to now see "Death Becomes Her." Trust me, you'll love it and you'll thank Sabrina Carpenter for showing it some love, because it's such an underrated romance horror classic.

comentario: Mmmm...the song explores the theme of jealousy and the lingering bond between ex-lovers... Sabrina is really addressing someone who has gotten back together with his ex, insinuating that, despite the new relationship, the author’s presence is still palpable. The line “You’ll just have to taste me when he’s kissin’ you” expresses the idea that, even though the relationship is over, the author is still a part of his ex’s life... so much so that the new partner cannot help but feel his presence! It is also very strong the way Sabrina emphasizes how some of his ex’s habits and behaviors, such as jokes or affectionate gestures, were learned from him (I am referring to “He’s funny, now all his jokes hit different / Guess who he learned that from?”). This lyric maybe could seem "trivial", but... it is very deep indeed 😊😊
